From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 38/42] web-app: configurable default chatmail relay for
 instant onboarding
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The welcome-screen "create new account" flow (instant onboarding, no
scanned QR) hardcoded upstream's default chatmail instance
(dcaccount:nine.testrun.org). Self-hosters running their own chatmail
relay had no way to send new sign-ups to it.

Add a slothfulInstanceConfig helper that parses
window.__slothfulConfig.defaultChatmailInstance (baked in via the
SLOTHFUL_DEFAULT_CHATMAIL build/customize variable) into the
dcaccount: QR to sign up with, plus a bare display host. It accepts a
bare host, a full URL, or a ready dcaccount: QR: bare hosts get any
path stripped (upstream's create-on-login form), full URLs are kept
whole (core POSTs to account-creation endpoints so the path must
survive), dcaccount: values pass through. Blank/degenerate values
return undefined so the caller falls back to the upstream default.

- useInstantOnboarding uses the configured QR as the default
  configuration QR; scanned dcaccount:/dclogin: QR codes still
  override it exactly as before.
- UserAgreement points the consent link at the configured relay and
  its /privacy.html (not upstream's nine.testrun.org policy) whenever
  the account is actually created on the configured default — i.e. the
  user didn't scan a specific account/login QR — so the privacy policy
  the user agrees to matches the relay the address is created on.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
